- Buster.

04:31.440 --> 04:36.640
- Mr. Joey Sweeney on the drums.
- Ow!

04:36.920 --> 04:39.196
Newly single, ladies.

04:39.400 --> 04:41.517
- Call me, Joe.
- And finally...

04:43.440 --> 04:46.194
...my right hand man,
Mr. Greg Sandoval...

04:46.400 --> 04:48.756
- ...and his sweet Gibson SG.
- Yeah.

04:48.920 --> 04:51.071
Whoo!

04:51.400 --> 04:53.119
And, you know, uh...

04:53.280 --> 04:56.432
I've been told it's not good
to date someone in the band...

04:56.640 --> 04:59.917
...but honestly, I don't think
it's hurting our sound, right?

05:00.120 --> 05:04.717
- We're not really dating, Greg.
- Oh.

05:04.880 --> 05:07.349
Excuse me, is that not
the correct terminology?

05:07.560 --> 05:09.711
Are we hooking up
like my kid says, right?

05:09.920 --> 05:10.956
Yes.

05:11.200 --> 05:12.236
Yeah, yeah.

05:12.680 --> 05:15.639
Well, we've been spending
some time together, yeah.

05:15.840 --> 05:18.753
I spend time with Buster.
I think you and I are different.

05:19.000 --> 05:20.593
Shit, I hope so. Shit.

05:20.840 --> 05:23.878
Okay, I think this is a conversation
for backstage.

05:24.080 --> 05:25.958
So let's just round it up, okay?

05:26.160 --> 05:28.994
We learned a tune
since our last gig at The Salt Well.

05:29.200 --> 05:32.591
Because some of you have asked
for more of today's hits.

05:32.800 --> 05:34.075
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

05:34.280 --> 05:37.432
- And we aim to please. Okay.
- Whoo!

05:46.720 --> 05:51.317
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh, oh
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

05:51.480 --> 05:54.279
♪ Caught in a bad romance ♪

05:54.480 --> 05:56.472
Come on, come on.

05:59.560 --> 06:02.519
♪ Caught in a bad romance ♪

06:03.360 --> 06:05.317
♪ Gaga, ha, ha, ha ♪

06:05.480 --> 06:07.073
♪ Roma, roma-ma ♪

06:07.240 --> 06:09.391
♪ Gaga, ooh, la, la ♪

06:09.560 --> 06:11.040
♪ I want your bad romance ♪

06:11.200 --> 06:12.998
♪ Rah, rah, ha, ha, ha ♪

06:13.200 --> 06:14.953
♪ Roma, roma-ma ♪

06:15.120 --> 06:16.793
♪ Gaga, ooh, la, la ♪ ♪

06:18.880 --> 06:21.475
Here you go, Ricki.
Margarita for my queen.

06:21.640 --> 06:24.951
- Oh. Thank you, darling.
- Yes, of course.

06:26.840 --> 06:29.594
Hey, Danny,
I'm sorry I couldn't talk before the gig.

06:29.800 --> 06:31.439
- Vocal rest.
- Oh, please.

06:31.640 --> 06:35.429
Vocal rest? She thinks this
is Madison Square Garden. Ha-ha-ha.

06:35.640 --> 06:37.199
- Hey, I...
- Great set, man.

06:37.400 --> 06:41.679
- I take things seriously, that's all.
- I know. I love that about you.

06:44.520 --> 06:46.876
I'm sorry that I, um...

06:47.320 --> 06:51.360
Sorry about what I said onstage.
That was just some fun banter. Heh, heh.

06:52.000 --> 06:55.914
You know, the crowd loves that drama
and tension. Yeah?

06:56.120 --> 06:58.760
- Good one.
- Thanks, boy.

06:59.840 --> 07:01.194
That was just, uh...

07:01.440 --> 07:04.399
Anyway, that was what made
Fleetwood Mac really popular.

07:04.600 --> 07:06.637
- Okay.
- Your purse is vibrating.

07:08.000 --> 07:10.595
If she moved with me,
she wouldn't need that kind of thing.

07:10.800 --> 07:13.918
It's probably my manager.
He's, like, 17.

07:15.320 --> 07:19.951
- Three-one-seven.
- Where's that? Bufu, Egypt?

07:20.160 --> 07:22.197
- It's Indianapolis.
- Hm.

07:22.400 --> 07:24.039
It's a telemarketer.

07:24.240 --> 07:27.711
I once got an Old Navy credit card.
It haunts me to this day.

07:27.960 --> 07:30.475
♪ Me man the milk
And I am the honey ♪

07:30.640 --> 07:32.950
♪ Me know him long time
From when him have no money ♪♪

07:33.120 --> 07:34.918
Our barista Maxine...

07:35.080 --> 07:36.673
...has delicious, dairy-free, premium...

07:36.880 --> 07:39.111
- Good morning.
- Hey.

07:40.880 --> 07:42.678
Good morning to you.

07:43.240 --> 07:45.391
Hey.

07:45.560 --> 07:47.950
It's ringing up. Okay.

07:48.160 --> 07:51.232
That's the way it goes. One.

07:53.960 --> 07:57.715
- Okay, that's 447.74.
- Ouch.

07:58.240 --> 08:01.597
I guess that's why they call it
"total paycheck."

08:01.800 --> 08:04.952
Well, that actually is truly
my total paycheck. Heh, heh.

08:05.120 --> 08:09.956
Four forty-seven, seventy-four.
That's about what I make in a week. Heh.

08:10.120 --> 08:12.316
- How about that?
- Ooh.

08:12.480 --> 08:15.837
And you'd like $150 cash back.

08:16.040 --> 08:17.440
Yes, please.

08:17.680 --> 08:20.400
Can an associate
meet a customer in frozen foods?

08:20.640 --> 08:22.950
There you go. There's your receipt.

08:23.160 --> 08:24.992
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much, sir.

08:25.160 --> 08:26.196
Have a good day.

08:26.400 --> 08:29.677
- Let me know how you like those cookies.
- Yeah, right.

08:32.360 --> 08:35.558
- Hey.
- You alienated the customer.

08:37.919 --> 08:41.231
- I...
- I need you to satisfy...

08:41.440 --> 08:43.557
...and delight the customer.

08:44.680 --> 08:46.512
Okay. I'm sorry, Troy.

08:46.720 --> 08:50.794
No, it's okay. Just remember, gratitude.

08:51.760 --> 08:54.355
- Cool. Thanks. Hi.
- Hi.

08:54.560 --> 08:56.153
Thanks.

09:22.160 --> 09:23.514
Come on.

09:27.840 --> 09:29.957
- Hello.
- Linda?

09:30.160 --> 09:32.391
You actually picked up.
I was expecting...

09:32.600 --> 09:35.638
...maybe you'd gotten, you know,
another new phone number.

09:35.880 --> 09:37.234
I'm sorry. I don't have...

09:37.440 --> 09:41.320
I can't figure out how to set up
the message box thing.

09:41.520 --> 09:43.591
You know me. Ha-ha-ha.

09:43.760 --> 09:45.319
Oh, yeah.

09:45.880 --> 09:46.996
Yeah.

09:47.360 --> 09:49.556
What's the problem, Pete?

09:49.760 --> 09:53.640
It's Julie. Max left her.

09:54.200 --> 09:56.112
Where'd he go?

09:56.800 --> 09:59.520
"Where'd he go?"
He left her. He's divorcing her.

09:59.720 --> 10:01.712
He met someone new.

10:01.920 --> 10:03.434
How is Julie?

10:03.640 --> 10:06.235
Well, that's really why I'm calling you.

10:06.440 --> 10:10.070
She's not well.
She's absolutely unhinged.

10:10.280 --> 10:12.749
She's been here at the house now
for a few days.

10:13.000 --> 10:15.799
She hasn't changed her clothes,
she hasn't showered.

10:16.040 --> 10:19.238
Uh, she's a wreck. I'm worried.

10:19.920 --> 10:24.153
Okay.
How is your wife handling all this?

10:24.360 --> 10:27.034
Maureen is in Seattle
visiting her father.

10:27.240 --> 10:30.392
- He is failing.
- Oh, right.

10:30.600 --> 10:32.478
He has Alzheimer's.

10:32.680 --> 10:35.320
No, it's ALS.

10:35.840 --> 10:38.799
Yeah, that's short for Alzheimer's, right?

10:39.200 --> 10:41.396
No, it's not.

10:41.840 --> 10:45.595
Okay, so how can I help?

10:46.120 --> 10:47.520
Well, um...

10:48.320 --> 10:51.040
...you could be there for your daughter.

10:55.360 --> 10:56.953
Linda?

11:05.360 --> 11:09.991
♪ You know
A train doesn't travel aimlessly ♪

11:13.960 --> 11:18.876
♪ No, it's got somewhere to go ♪

11:19.360 --> 11:21.591
Oh, yeah.

11:25.760 --> 11:28.719
Please have IDs
and tickets ready to view.

11:28.920 --> 11:30.593
Belts and shoes off, please.

11:30.800 --> 11:33.998
If you have a laptop,
please put it in a bin by itself.

11:34.640 --> 11:39.271
Please take your keys, cell phones
and metal objects out of your pockets.

11:43.120 --> 11:47.353
♪ If you wanna take, you gotta give ♪

11:47.560 --> 11:51.520
♪ And regret is no way to live ♪

11:51.680 --> 11:56.072
♪ You can't forget if you want to forgive ♪

11:56.240 --> 11:59.597
♪ So I'll claim what's mine ♪

11:59.760 --> 12:06.030
♪ With a little spit and shine
We'll be fine ♪♪

12:06.280 --> 12:09.796
- Who are you dropping off?
- Uh, Ricki Rendazzo.

12:16.000 --> 12:17.559
And you're here to see...?

12:17.720 --> 12:19.712
The Brummels. Pete Brummel.

12:20.480 --> 12:21.800
Can I see some ID?

12:22.000 --> 12:24.754
- What?
- ID, ma'am.

12:29.320 --> 12:30.595
Here you go.

12:31.160 --> 12:32.753
Thank you.

12:35.800 --> 12:37.837
This says "Linda."

12:38.040 --> 12:42.273
Yeah, that's my given name, but Pete
knows that I prefer to go by Ricki...

12:42.480 --> 12:45.040
- ...so I'm sure he'll probably...
- Here you are.

12:45.240 --> 12:46.674
Linda Brummel.

13:11.400 --> 13:13.039
Oh.

13:16.920 --> 13:18.115
I don't have any money.

13:21.080 --> 13:22.196
Let me.

13:22.440 --> 13:25.353
Here. I'll get those.

13:26.440 --> 13:29.353
Hey, who is this?

13:29.560 --> 13:31.313
Is this Ralphie?

13:31.520 --> 13:33.193
No, that's Sigma.

13:33.400 --> 13:35.392
Ralphie passed away a few years ago.

13:35.600 --> 13:37.717
- Excess bloat.
- Aw.

13:38.200 --> 13:40.556
Well, then we're new
to each other, huh?

13:40.760 --> 13:42.319
How was your flight?

13:42.560 --> 13:48.716
It was fine, but travel has really changed
since we took the kids to Disney World.

13:48.920 --> 13:50.673
That was 1988.

13:50.880 --> 13:53.236
Yeah. No, I just mean, you know...

13:53.440 --> 13:56.751
I remember when flying was a treat.
People got dressed up even.

13:56.960 --> 14:00.431
Now I see these young girls in the airport
in their jammy bottoms.

14:00.640 --> 14:04.554
Yeah. Well, I can see
you still put in the effort.

14:04.760 --> 14:07.229
Thanks, Pete.

14:07.520 --> 14:09.193
This is some place.

14:09.400 --> 14:11.437
This is like a mansion.

14:11.640 --> 14:14.872
Thanks.
Yeah, well, double-height entry...

14:15.080 --> 14:18.437
...and Maureen had to have Palladian
windows, so we put those in.

14:18.600 --> 14:19.636
Very classical.

14:19.800 --> 14:22.998
Yeah. I feel like Jefferson at Monticello.

14:23.200 --> 14:25.840
- I'll go tell Julie you're here.
- Heh, heh.

14:26.000 --> 14:28.117
Okay. I'll just have a look around.

14:28.320 --> 14:30.471
Okay. Julie?

14:32.280 --> 14:35.352
Oh, my God.

14:53.960 --> 14:56.634
Look at this place.

15:02.200 --> 15:03.759
Mm-hm.

15:05.280 --> 15:06.680
Mm-hm.

15:15.280 --> 15:18.000
Mm. My, my, my.

15:19.280 --> 15:20.999
Wow.

15:25.800 --> 15:28.076
Man.

15:49.160 --> 15:53.632
Uh, Julie's pretty tired.
But she's glad you're here...

15:53.840 --> 15:56.400
...and looks forward to seeing you
in the morning.

15:56.640 --> 15:58.233
Wrong. No, no, no.

15:58.440 --> 16:02.753
Julie is not looking forward to shit!

16:04.280 --> 16:06.158
Hey, Ju-jee.

16:06.360 --> 16:08.716
Nice of you to grace us
with your presence.

16:08.880 --> 16:12.760
Couldn't make the wedding, but here
you are right in time for the divorce.

16:12.920 --> 16:16.038
Okay. Nobody wanted me
at that wedding.

16:16.280 --> 16:19.432
Do you have a gig or do you always
dress like a hooker from Night Court?

16:21.680 --> 16:24.957
Going through a separation,
it can be a crazy time.

16:25.160 --> 16:28.836
I'm not crazy, Dad.
I've actually never felt such clarity.

16:29.040 --> 16:31.509
Well, there's actually a book
called Crazy Time.

16:31.760 --> 16:34.514
- Oh, shut up, Pete!
- Honey, listen.

16:34.760 --> 16:38.231
This whole thing is not a big deal.

16:38.400 --> 16:41.757
- I read something in Parade magazine.
- No big deal?

16:41.960 --> 16:43.394
A lot of women your age...

16:43.640 --> 16:47.919
- ...having starter marriages and...
- This was not a "starter" marriage.

16:48.120 --> 16:50.715
I was gonna marry Max,
stay with him, have kids...

16:50.920 --> 16:53.355
...and actually raise them to adulthood.

16:53.560 --> 16:56.394
Oh, okay. Julie, just take it easy.

16:56.600 --> 16:58.159
Why are you defending her?

16:58.360 --> 16:59.760
- She is your Max.
- What?

16:59.960 --> 17:02.316
- She walked out on you...
- Hey, no.

17:02.520 --> 17:07.675
- ...just like Max walked out on me.
- But I was never unfaithful, Julie.

17:13.960 --> 17:15.713
Ju-jee...

17:32.360 --> 17:33.919
So, um...

17:36.440 --> 17:39.638
- We'll try again in the morning.
- Yeah, of course.

17:40.240 --> 17:43.438
I'll, uh, give you a ride to the hotel.

17:45.160 --> 17:46.560
Oh...

17:46.720 --> 17:48.871
Oh. Ha-ha-ha.

17:49.040 --> 17:52.158
I... I'm so sorry.

17:54.520 --> 17:57.354
I could hardly afford the plane ticket,
you know?

17:57.560 --> 17:59.119
And, uh...

17:59.640 --> 18:01.677
- Well, you know, I lost my car.
- Yeah.

18:01.880 --> 18:04.554
- I'm filing for chapter 11.
- I know.

18:04.760 --> 18:08.913
So I just thought since you and Maureen
built this big, new house...

18:09.120 --> 18:12.716
- ...that it wouldn't be a problem.
- It's not a problem, space-wise.

18:12.920 --> 18:13.956
It's, uh...

18:14.160 --> 18:15.753
It's just...

18:16.640 --> 18:18.916
I don't know, a boundary thing.

18:19.160 --> 18:22.437
- But it's fine.
- Mm.

18:23.680 --> 18:25.990
Hope Maureen doesn't mind.

18:26.200 --> 18:28.271
No, Mo's very chill.

18:28.480 --> 18:31.678
I'm the one that tends to get worked up
about certain things.

18:31.920 --> 18:34.037
Maybe Julie gets that from you.

18:36.120 --> 18:39.557
- The bathroom is en suite.
- Oh.

18:39.760 --> 18:40.989
Okay.

18:41.200 --> 18:43.840
So, um, welcome.

18:44.040 --> 18:45.633
Sigma, come.

18:45.840 --> 18:47.320
Come.

18:49.240 --> 18:51.197
- I trained her myself.
- Heh-heh-heh.

18:51.440 --> 18:53.193
Okay, well...

18:53.600 --> 18:54.954
- Welcome.
- Okay.

18:55.160 --> 18:56.879
Good night, Linda.

18:57.080 --> 18:59.675
Good night, Pete.

19:55.000 --> 19:56.036
Linda.

19:57.400 --> 19:59.392
- Linda!
- Huh?

20:02.280 --> 20:04.476
I was a real bitch last night, huh?

20:04.720 --> 20:08.634
Well, it was late. Heh.

20:09.400 --> 20:13.713
My therapist has me on Effexor,
and we need to titrate down a little bit...

20:13.920 --> 20:17.630
...because it's made me volatile,
anorgasmic.

20:18.440 --> 20:20.352
You're having orgasms?

20:20.560 --> 20:22.950
Anorgasmic. "An" means "not."

20:23.200 --> 20:24.520
- It's Latin.
- Oh, I...

20:24.720 --> 20:27.315
Yeah, I know. I knew that.
I just didn't hear you.

20:27.520 --> 20:29.398
- What time is it?
- It's almost 10.

20:34.040 --> 20:35.679
Blowing up here, Mom.

20:36.320 --> 20:38.152
Who's Greg?

20:38.360 --> 20:42.240
He's the lead guitarist in The Flash.

20:42.440 --> 20:43.715
The Flash?

20:43.920 --> 20:45.354
My band, The Flash.

20:45.560 --> 20:48.473
I sent you the Facebook page
a long time ago, remember?

20:48.720 --> 20:50.200
Give me the phone.

20:50.400 --> 20:52.915
- He calls you "babe."
- Yeah, that's an L.A. thing.

20:53.080 --> 20:57.233
Uh-huh. He also makes copious use
of the smiley face emoji.

20:57.480 --> 21:00.518
As well as the cat
with the hearts for eyes.

21:01.080 --> 21:04.551
- How long has Greg been getting it in?
- Hey, let's go to Krupke's.

21:06.000 --> 21:07.957
I need a doughnut.

21:15.280 --> 21:18.876
Uh, I don't have any money.

21:19.080 --> 21:20.480
You have a credit card?

21:20.640 --> 21:22.677
Yeah, but it's linked
to Max's account.

21:23.120 --> 21:25.715
Oh, that's not a problem.

21:25.880 --> 21:27.394
Hop in.

21:31.800 --> 21:34.554
♪ So you do what you gotta do ♪

21:39.040 --> 21:42.112
♪ Come on, girl, walk on ♪

21:44.360 --> 21:48.752
♪ I know you're fighting an uphill battle ♪

21:48.920 --> 21:52.675
♪ But you'll win with a little struggle ♪

21:53.240 --> 21:57.951
♪ 'Cause you're really not that fragile
So walk on ♪♪

22:07.400 --> 22:12.236
You know, it's hard to find a good cruller
in California. Heh, heh.

22:13.560 --> 22:18.635
I guess you got to give up a lot
of special things to become a rock star.

22:23.120 --> 22:25.510
Crullers were the least of it.

22:25.880 --> 22:28.759
Yeah, Linda, that was the subtext.

22:38.320 --> 22:41.472
Listen, honey, I came out here
because I wanted to help you.

22:42.640 --> 22:45.314
I know you're in shock right now, right?

22:45.520 --> 22:48.160
And I know
you're probably feeling lost.

22:48.360 --> 22:50.556
I tried to kill myself.

22:50.920 --> 22:52.752
You... You...

22:56.120 --> 22:58.555
Hm. Dad didn't mention that.

22:58.720 --> 23:01.030
Oh. Really?

23:01.800 --> 23:06.829
Three Fridays ago, Max told me that
he was in love with a girl named Nicole...

23:07.040 --> 23:08.997
...who works in traffic.

23:09.640 --> 23:12.439
- Julie...
- I thought for a while about what to do...

23:12.640 --> 23:15.712
...and ultimately, I decided...

23:17.120 --> 23:19.510
...to take a bunch of sleeping pills.

23:20.200 --> 23:22.795
I had them on hand
because I'm an insomniac.

23:23.760 --> 23:25.638
Like me.

23:26.080 --> 23:28.595
And millions of other Americans, yeah.

23:36.040 --> 23:37.997
What are you doing?

23:39.600 --> 23:43.389
I can't believe...
I can't believe you tried to kill yourself.

23:43.600 --> 23:46.877
