25:38.040 --> 25:41.238
- Yup.
- You came back here from California...

25:41.440 --> 25:42.476
...if you recall...

25:42.720 --> 25:45.679
...with a chip on your shoulder.
You were shut down.

25:45.880 --> 25:47.473
- Well, I did come back.
- Well...

25:47.640 --> 25:50.553
- You had moved on.
- I had to move on.

25:50.760 --> 25:53.639
I wanted the kids to have a mother
who was there!

25:53.840 --> 25:56.196
- It was my dream, man.
- And stupid me.

25:56.400 --> 26:00.030
- I thought we were your dream.
- I can't have two dreams?

26:00.280 --> 26:04.115
- No. In fact, Linda, you can't.
- Hey, you guys are fighting.

26:04.320 --> 26:06.596
It's like the '80s all over again.

26:06.800 --> 26:08.757
Too bad Adam and Josh aren't here
to relive the trauma.

26:09.000 --> 26:11.754
- Oh, good grief. Oh.
- That's enough.

26:13.000 --> 26:17.313
Speaking of, uh, Josh and Adam, um...

26:17.520 --> 26:20.240
...I let both the boys know
that you came into town.

26:20.440 --> 26:21.874
Oh, g...

26:22.080 --> 26:24.959
- Do they wanna see me?
- Josh does.

26:25.160 --> 26:26.196
Adam doesn't.

26:26.400 --> 26:28.869
In fact,
they're up for dinner this evening.

26:29.080 --> 26:33.120
Josh is gonna bring his girlfriend, Emily.
They've gotten pretty close.

26:33.320 --> 26:37.439
- Mm. Is Adam bringing anybody?
- I...

26:38.400 --> 26:40.153
I don't think so.

26:41.040 --> 26:45.080
Well, I'll have all my kids in one room.

26:46.880 --> 26:48.678
- What a treat.
- Yeah.

26:48.880 --> 26:51.111
It should be really enjoyable.

26:53.840 --> 26:54.990
Hey, here's Ricki.

26:55.200 --> 26:56.839
Oh, tell her we love her.

26:57.040 --> 26:59.600
I gotta be careful with the L word.
She's gun shy.

26:59.840 --> 27:01.638
Oh, you'll get there.

27:02.720 --> 27:06.634
- Hey, babe.
- So, uh, my daughter, Julie...

27:06.840 --> 27:09.480
...she apparently, uh...

27:12.040 --> 27:14.430
She tried to kill herself
with sleeping pills.

27:16.080 --> 27:18.515
Oh, man.

27:18.720 --> 27:21.189
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Whoa.

27:21.400 --> 27:23.119
How is she?

27:23.800 --> 27:26.554
Oh, no, no, she's okay. She's okay.

27:26.760 --> 27:29.070
- But, uh...
- I don't know what to say.

27:29.280 --> 27:32.114
I mean, you know my son, Derek,
freaked out on acid...

27:32.320 --> 27:35.518
- ...but it was an accident.
- I blame myself.

27:35.720 --> 27:36.790
No way.

27:37.000 --> 27:39.356
Blame that punk that cheated on her.

27:39.560 --> 27:43.270
You got on the plane to Indiana
to be by her side. You're a great mom.

27:43.480 --> 27:44.480
Oh...

27:44.680 --> 27:47.798
I'm seeing my boys tonight.

27:48.000 --> 27:49.400
Oh, that's great.

27:49.640 --> 27:50.915
Enjoy it, okay?

27:51.120 --> 27:53.510
I'm scared. I'm just...

27:53.920 --> 27:57.709
- They're all grown up now.
- No.

27:58.080 --> 28:00.834
No, you grow them, you know them.

28:01.120 --> 28:04.397
They're the same kids whose diapers
you changed way back when.

28:06.240 --> 28:07.310
Enjoy it.

28:07.520 --> 28:12.231
- Mr. Brummel, it's nice to see you.
- Hi, Mabel. Nice to see you.

28:12.560 --> 28:14.870
- Thanks for squeezing us in.
- Anytime.

28:15.080 --> 28:18.152
- Your party is waiting. Yup, follow me.
- Oh, okay.

28:18.360 --> 28:20.477
Five minutes late.

28:32.480 --> 28:35.040
Yeah. So now we have to...

28:38.200 --> 28:40.078
Here she comes.

28:40.800 --> 28:41.836
Oh, boy.

28:45.480 --> 28:47.517
Josh. Hey.

28:47.720 --> 28:50.519
- Hi, Mom.
- Aw.

28:51.440 --> 28:53.033
Josh.

28:53.240 --> 28:55.277
- This is my girlfriend, Emily.
- Hi.

28:55.480 --> 28:57.870
It's a pleasure
to finally meet you, Linda.

28:58.080 --> 29:00.720
- Yeah.
- Hey, hey. That's Ricki Rendazzo.

29:00.960 --> 29:03.350
You're in the presence of greatness.
Don't forget.

29:03.520 --> 29:04.920
Heh. Adam.

29:05.120 --> 29:07.430
You look so handsome, sweetie.

29:07.680 --> 29:09.717
Oh, thanks, Mom.

29:09.920 --> 29:12.389
Why don't you take that seat?
We can flank them.

29:12.960 --> 29:15.634
- Good to see you. Sorry we're late.
- Yeah, you are.

29:15.840 --> 29:17.877
Nice to see you're so punctual.

29:18.080 --> 29:19.230
It's okay.

29:19.480 --> 29:22.632
Can I get you some drinks?
Would you like another martini?

29:22.840 --> 29:24.991
Yeah. Why not? Keep them coming.

29:25.240 --> 29:27.471
- I'll just have water.
- Me too, water.

29:27.960 --> 29:29.838
With Scotch.

29:42.560 --> 29:44.313
So, um...

29:46.200 --> 29:47.793
How is Maureen's father doing?

29:48.520 --> 29:49.670
Oh, not well at all.

29:50.120 --> 29:53.909
No, the disease is progressing
more rapidly than they'd anticipated.

29:54.120 --> 29:56.077
So you've met Maureen?

29:56.280 --> 29:57.680
Yeah, of course.

29:57.880 --> 29:59.473
Lots of times. Heh, heh.

29:59.680 --> 30:00.796
Mo's great.

30:01.000 --> 30:03.276
- Yeah.
- Yeah, she's...

30:03.480 --> 30:06.917
Emily and I have been together
for almost two years.

30:07.120 --> 30:09.919
- She's met the whole family.
- Yup.

30:10.360 --> 30:13.114
- Yeah.
- Em, why aren't you wearing your ring?

30:15.680 --> 30:17.512
Your engagement ring.

30:19.600 --> 30:21.876
You two are engaged?

30:22.120 --> 30:23.600
Yes.

30:23.840 --> 30:25.115
- Yup.
- Yeah.

30:25.320 --> 30:27.516
Josh got Emily
this conflict-free diamond.

30:27.760 --> 30:30.036
He proposed at the lake.
We were all there.

30:30.240 --> 30:31.720
It was beyond gay.

30:33.720 --> 30:36.474
- It was lovely. It was lovely.
- I'm happy for you.

30:36.640 --> 30:39.314
So happy for you, honey.

30:39.560 --> 30:42.553
- Thank you.
- Why didn't you tell me?

30:43.000 --> 30:45.879
Well, we, uh, wanted to keep
things quiet for a while...

30:46.080 --> 30:50.552
- ...so we could enjoy the news privately.
- Oh.

30:50.760 --> 30:53.195
But Julie said everybody
was at the proposal.

30:53.400 --> 30:55.232
Did this just happen?

30:55.440 --> 30:57.557
- Yeah. Yeah.
- No. No, it was...

30:57.760 --> 30:59.672
- No. It was July 4th.
- Yeah.

31:00.720 --> 31:03.599
So that was months.

31:03.840 --> 31:05.194
Months ago.

31:05.400 --> 31:08.791
We all know you're going through
something, but you're cray-cray.

31:09.000 --> 31:11.834
We were planning on
telling you tonight in person.

31:12.040 --> 31:13.633
Because I hadn't met you and...

31:13.840 --> 31:18.039
Why don't you be honest and tell Mom
that you don't want her at the wedding?

31:21.120 --> 31:24.158
Would you be interested
in hearing our appetizer specials?

31:24.400 --> 31:26.039
- Yes.
- No.

31:26.280 --> 31:28.556
We're practically eloping, Mom.

31:28.760 --> 31:32.515
Yeah, it's gonna be very small,
very green.

31:32.720 --> 31:35.952
Not gonna be a big, formal wedding
like the one Julie had.

31:36.200 --> 31:39.272
- Thanks for referencing that.
- Yeah, well, thanks for this.

31:39.480 --> 31:42.314
I'm still having Ambien shits
from my suicide attempt.

31:42.520 --> 31:45.638
- You wanna talk about my wedding?
- It's okay. Go ahead.

31:45.880 --> 31:49.112
You know, it won't hurt my feelings
if you decide to elope.

31:49.320 --> 31:50.834
Your dad and I eloped.

31:51.040 --> 31:53.839
- It was great.
- Yes, it was.

31:54.520 --> 31:58.070
Yeah. So, anyway,
this is wonderful, wonderful news.

31:58.280 --> 31:59.953
- Thank you.
- Wonderful.

32:00.160 --> 32:03.437
Hey, Adam, when are you gonna
settle down and get married?

32:03.640 --> 32:05.359
Who wants some appetizers?

32:05.560 --> 32:08.712
- Mom, I'm gay, as you know.
- You used to love the carpaccio.

32:09.080 --> 32:10.355
And unfortunately...

32:10.560 --> 32:13.473
...many of my fellow gay men
still can't get married.

32:13.680 --> 32:16.991
Well, I didn't mean to a man
necessarily.

32:17.240 --> 32:21.029
- Who would I marry, then?
- Well, I thought you were bisexual.

32:21.240 --> 32:25.120
That was my cover story in college,
like, 10 years ago.

32:25.320 --> 32:29.633
I'm really sorry that you didn't stay
updated on my sexuality...

32:29.880 --> 32:33.874
...but then again, you didn't stay updated
on much of anything. Am I right?

32:34.080 --> 32:38.233
Okay. Okay. Now that I know that you
decided to say you're completely gay...

32:38.440 --> 32:42.150
- "Decided"? You are such a homophobe.
- ...I won't ask about it again.

32:42.360 --> 32:45.990
This is what she does. She costumes
herself as this edgy rocker...

32:46.200 --> 32:48.510
...who's cooler
than the other PTA moms...

32:48.720 --> 32:51.713
...when in fact,
she voted for George W. Bush twice.

32:51.920 --> 32:53.274
I support our troops.

32:53.480 --> 32:55.790
And I'm the one
with the questionable lifestyle.

32:55.960 --> 32:59.112
Huh? Meanwhile, she's running around
calling herself Ricki.

32:59.320 --> 33:01.994
Well, that's a name, not a lifestyle.

33:02.200 --> 33:03.759
I was born gay.

33:04.000 --> 33:06.117
I was born Ricki.

33:07.800 --> 33:09.439
Touché.

33:09.640 --> 33:12.394
This shit-show is making my day.

33:12.600 --> 33:15.718
Is this whole thing a plea for attention
as per usual...

33:15.920 --> 33:18.151
...or are you actually a psychotic bitch?

33:18.360 --> 33:21.398
Hey, don't you dare call your sister
psychotic!

33:24.640 --> 33:27.838
Oh, my God, she's parenting.
Someone get a camera.

33:28.040 --> 33:30.794
Just cool it. This...

33:31.160 --> 33:33.311
Let's... Look.

33:33.720 --> 33:38.840
It's a very rare occasion
that we all get together like this.

33:39.040 --> 33:40.713
Your mother's here, right?

33:41.120 --> 33:44.796
I mean, I know...
I know we've always had...

33:45.040 --> 33:48.033
...some, you know,
issues and personality conflicts...

33:48.240 --> 33:50.675
- ...but what family hasn't?
- Yeah.

33:50.920 --> 33:53.640
But we are a family, still.

33:53.880 --> 33:57.351
You know, let's... We can put
all that crap behind us, can't we?

33:57.560 --> 34:00.997
And just appreciate the proximity.

34:01.480 --> 34:04.791
I mean, at this moment,
the Brummel family and family-to-be...

34:05.000 --> 34:07.560
...is proximal.

34:07.760 --> 34:10.480
That's special in itself, isn't it?

34:10.679 --> 34:11.830
Thank you.

34:12.040 --> 34:14.554
I would get a bottle of champagne
for the whole table.

34:15.960 --> 34:20.112
- No, but that's...
- But I just filed for bankruptcy.

34:20.320 --> 34:22.072
Describe to me how it makes you...

34:22.280 --> 34:24.158
Well, doc...

34:24.360 --> 34:26.112
And thank you for asking.

34:26.320 --> 34:30.438
It's not that I feel unbreakable
or even impenetrable.

34:30.639 --> 34:31.994
It's just...

34:32.199 --> 34:35.112
What is it? Come on, Angelo.

34:35.320 --> 34:37.994
This is a major breakthrough here.

35:02.320 --> 35:05.518
There is a wonderful,
old Italian joke about a poor man...

35:05.720 --> 35:06.836
You're still here?

35:07.880 --> 35:09.678
Hey.

35:13.240 --> 35:15.709
What are we gonna do today?

35:18.320 --> 35:20.152
I have therapy at noon...

35:20.360 --> 35:24.320
...so I gotta go wash my dick...

35:24.520 --> 35:27.319
...or I'll get another lecture
in personal care.

35:27.560 --> 35:29.870
Why don't you skip therapy?

35:30.080 --> 35:31.673
Just today.

35:31.880 --> 35:33.075
Call in sick.

35:34.120 --> 35:35.474
I am sick.

35:35.680 --> 35:38.752
That's why I'm in therapy.

35:38.960 --> 35:41.600
I mean, how often am I here? Heh.

35:44.800 --> 35:46.393
Never?

35:49.440 --> 35:50.840
Honestly.

35:51.200 --> 35:53.431
It's just a shampoo and trim.

35:53.640 --> 35:56.792
You have really good hair.
You should, like, brush it.

35:57.000 --> 35:58.992
She has my hair.

35:59.200 --> 36:01.157
Ow! Unh!

36:01.720 --> 36:05.111
Not more than half an inch.
I can feel how much you're cutting.

36:05.320 --> 36:07.880
Why are we so attached to our hair?

36:08.080 --> 36:11.357
Someday you're gonna find a gray hair,
and I don't mean on your head.

36:15.080 --> 36:17.754
No one wants to hear
about your steel wool, Mom.

36:23.760 --> 36:25.877
I look like Nosferatu.

36:26.120 --> 36:28.794
Oh, don't worry, they file them down.

36:29.800 --> 36:33.714
That's 190 on the card
and you can add whatever tip.

36:33.960 --> 36:36.600
Let's leave a nice, big one, shall we?

36:47.640 --> 36:49.154
Hey.

36:51.640 --> 36:52.835
Hey.

36:58.520 --> 37:01.831
You look very nice.

37:03.520 --> 37:06.319
Well... How?

37:11.040 --> 37:14.272
I just made a suggestion, you know?

37:15.320 --> 37:17.437
- She listens to me.
- Huh.

37:19.440 --> 37:22.353
I was a bit of a jerk yesterday.
I'm sorry about that.

37:22.560 --> 37:24.950
The market had... The...

37:25.160 --> 37:28.119
Things have been really stressful
at the company.

37:28.320 --> 37:32.280
Yeah, well, you work very hard.
I admire that.

37:32.520 --> 37:33.795
- You do?
- Yeah.

37:34.000 --> 37:37.789
You used to call me
an uptight workaholic.

37:38.000 --> 37:39.275
Yeah, honey.

37:39.520 --> 37:42.433
- I used to call you a lot of things.
- Heh, heh.

37:42.600 --> 37:44.751
But I changed, Pete.

37:44.960 --> 37:45.996
I have.

37:46.760 --> 37:48.513
I see that.

37:48.720 --> 37:53.158
I mean, I've been trying to get her
to change her clothes for days.

37:53.360 --> 37:56.637
Well, sometimes a girl
just needs her mother.

37:56.960 --> 37:58.713
I guess so.

38:01.240 --> 38:04.199
- Here we go. Taste it.
- They changed it a little.

38:04.400 --> 38:06.119
No, no, it's the same taste.

38:06.320 --> 38:09.313
- It's... Why would they change it?
- No. I don't know why.

38:09.520 --> 38:11.671
- Holy shit.
- It's a recipe that has...

38:11.880 --> 38:13.712
Oh, my God.

38:14.960 --> 38:18.032
- What?
- Nicole from traffic. This is her car.

38:18.240 --> 38:20.118
But you can't be sure.

38:20.360 --> 38:21.589
No, I know.

38:21.800 --> 38:24.952
She's got
these stupid stick figure thing...

38:28.640 --> 38:29.915
Oh, baby.

38:30.680 --> 38:33.240
Oh, she added Max. Oh, my God.

38:33.680 --> 38:37.720
- Let's not vandalize the car. Come on.
- Hey, hey! Let's just go home, all right?

38:37.960 --> 38:39.553
Let's go home.

38:50.840 --> 38:56.120
♪ So if you're feeling low
Turn up your radio ♪

38:58.800 --> 39:00.234
No, no, no, Julie.

39:00.480 --> 39:02.597
Please, Julie. Julie, wait.

39:09.200 --> 39:11.669
♪ Won't you dance with me? ♪

39:11.960 --> 39:13.553
♪ Yeah ♪

39:13.920 --> 39:15.798
♪ Rip it up ♪♪

39:16.600 --> 39:19.638
Why did you walk out
on my daughter that way?

39:19.840 --> 39:23.834
- I made a mistake. Got married young.
- If you're too young to be married...

39:24.040 --> 39:27.556
...what makes you think that you're ready
to raise Kenzie and Krash?

39:27.800 --> 39:30.190
It's Kash,
and how do you know my kids' names?

39:30.400 --> 39:33.154
Everybody on Highway 70
knows your kids' names.

39:33.320 --> 39:35.312
Lady, you weren't even
at our wedding.

39:38.320 --> 39:40.960
Julie hates you.

39:41.880 --> 39:44.600
That may be.
I have to live with that every day.

39:44.800 --> 39:46.951
You have to live
with the pain you caused.

39:47.160 --> 39:49.880
- You're the reason she's crazy.
- Julie's not crazy.

39:50.080 --> 39:54.836
Julie is grieving over a very short
marriage to a man who turns out...

39:55.080 --> 39:57.231
That's enough.
You two need to back off.

39:57.440 --> 40:00.831
You. You know, it's one thing
to fall in love with somebody.

40:01.080 --> 40:05.518
It's quite another to encourage him
to abandon his new wife...

40:05.720 --> 40:10.351
...and then slapping a sticker of him
on the back of your car next to the dog.

40:10.560 --> 40:12.597
Hey, I love my dog, okay?

40:12.840 --> 40:14.832
Yeah? Now you have two.

40:15.000 --> 40:16.354
Oh.

40:19.400 --> 40:21.312
Whoo!

40:24.600 --> 40:27.718
- My heart is dead and rotten.
- Don't say that.

40:27.920 --> 40:33.075
No, a heart isn't something
that's like a steak, you know, that spoils.

40:33.320 --> 40:35.676
A heart is like a Big Mac.

40:35.880 --> 40:38.349
It just sits and sits and sits.

40:38.560 --> 40:41.712
It gets older, yeah,
but it doesn't change.

40:41.960 --> 40:45.431
What? You're saying that
a Big Mac never goes bad?

40:45.640 --> 40:48.155
Yeah, that's what I'm saying.

40:48.360 --> 40:51.592
- Interesting.
- It lives forever.

40:51.840 --> 40:53.832
I saw it on 60 Minutes.

40:54.040 --> 40:58.193
- That's disgusting.
- Huh. Well, hm, hm, hm.

40:59.080 --> 41:00.753
But I say... Yeah.

41:00.960 --> 41:03.520
- Yeah, I...
- Everybody hitting the hay?

41:03.800 --> 41:05.837
- Dad.
- Yeah?

41:06.040 --> 41:10.273
It's not even 9 p.m.
I don't think that even Oma is in bed.

41:10.480 --> 41:12.039
- Hey, Pete.
- Yeah?

41:12.280 --> 41:15.034
Why is there pot in your freezer?

41:15.880 --> 41:18.156
Uh... It was a...

41:18.360 --> 41:21.114
A coworker gave it to me
